Subject: Re: [T2] Exhausts that delete the heaterboxes completely on 

Mike S wrote:
>
> Why? If you don't want to hook up all the heater stuff, don't. What 
> harm do the heater boxes do just sitting there? Actually, used that 
> way, they may give a slight performance increase vs. plain pipes, by 
> keeping the exhaust hot and flowing, and pushing that heat further 
> away from the engine.

Actually, different people have repeatedly said on shoptalkforums that 
the heater boxes (the late bay version) are the biggest problem for the 
t4 engine in respect to excessive head temps and performance.  They say 
the early exchangers that bolt directly to the heads help things flow 
much better.

